        <h3>Trying Out</h3>

        <p>
            Tryouts will be held in 20 minute sessions at <a href="http://www.vatechniques.com/">Virginia Techniques</a>. 
            <a href="/home/index/#directions">Directions to Virginia Techniques</a> may be found on 
            our <a href="/home/index">Home page</a>.
        </p>

        <h4>Format</h4>

        <ol>
            <li>Attire consists of a sports bra, spandex shorts, cheer shoes, and a collegiate appearance</li>
            <li>Arrive 20 minutes prior to your assigned session to stretch and prepare</li>
            <li>During your assigned session you will perform
                <ul>
                    <li>Jumps to tumbling</li>
                    <li>Standing tumbling</li>
                    <li>Standing series tumbling pass</li>
                    <li>Running tumbling pass</li>
                    <li>Stunting with previous team members</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Please leave the gym at the conclusion of your assigned session</li>
            <li>Results will be emailed the night of tryouts</li>
        </ol>

        <p>
            Following Fall tryouts, the coaching staff will designate alternate positions. The coaching staff reserves
            the right to make further cuts, as necessary.
        </p>

        <p>
            <strong>Note: </strong>Cheerleading is a subjective sport. The decision of the coaching staff is final.
